The paper deals with algorithmic techniques for solving geometric data management and analysis problems, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of data structures such as segment tree and range tree suggests that it may also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The mention of data management problems suggests that it may belong to the databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The mention of analysis problems suggests that it may belong to the data mining (cs.DM) sub-category. Finally, the use of algorithmic techniques suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
